FBIS4-42277 "drweu105_q_94013" FBIS-WEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 TURKEY Dev-Sol Members, Islamic Militants Caught in Ankara Dev-Sol Members, Islamic Militants Caught in Ankara TA0106072794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 2000 GMT 31 May 94 TA0106072794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network Turkish BFN [Text] Thirteen members of an illegal leftist organization and four members of a radical religious organization were caught in Ankara. In a news conference, Ankara Security Director Orhan Tasanlar said that the suspects belonging to Dev-Sol [Revolutionary Left] posted placards, distributed pamphlets, and threw Molotov cocktails on various dates. Tasanlar reported that the suspects belonging to the illegal Islamic Great Vanguards Front [Islami Buyuk Akincilar Cephesi] threw bombs at various places in Ankara. One pistol, large quantities of material used in the manufacturing of time bombs, and organizational documents were also seized.
